    <note>Wei(5) Guan [1945] His ancestors were Julu jun Wei(5) and later Guantao Wei(5). See Chen Shidao's funerary inscription for details of lineage history after early Tang zaixiang, Zheng. Guan moved from Huizhou to Shouzhou, Xiacai xian where he was buried, thereby establishing the Xiacai Wei(5) lineage branch of the clan. Yu's [1949] son, Yan's [7390] brother, Zhang(1) Mian's [262] brother-in-law. His first and second wives were both daughters of Diao(1) Yan [3847], who was the younger brother of Guan's mother, and his son Shao's [4205] son-in-law was Diao(1) Baochen [3843]. Another of Shao's sons-in-law was Chao(2) Zongque's [8001] great grandson, Chao(2) Zaizhi [3020]. Chen Shidao, WJ, 16.2a-2b; XCB, 116.20a; Xinan zhi, 6.19b; Huang Tingjian, WJ, 24.2a-3b; Guangxi TZ, 16.13a; SS, 303.2b-3a. CBD, 5, 4241.</note>
